Last night (December 30) began, Wuhan appeared a number of cases of unexplained pneumonia news began to circulate. This morning, Jian Wen called the Wuhan Center for Disease Control and Prevention at 8:00 a.m. , and the staff told us:

Still can not confirm is SARS, the patient has been quarantined, the health commission experts have come to Wuhan, do not panic.

Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome, Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome, severe infectious disease caused by the SARS coronavirus (SARS-cov) , which can infect humans or animals and is highly infectious and deadly, and many patients die quickly in the early stages of infection.

Since November 2002, SARS has spread rapidly to dozens of countries and regions around the world. As of July 2003, the number of cases worldwide reached 8,098, including 774 deaths, with a global case fatality rate of nearly 10% , nearly half of those who died were older than 65. In China, the SARS epidemic started in Guangdong, and Beijing is the most serious, with the nationwide strict control, patient isolation treatment, the epidemic was quickly contained. In 2003, the epidemic situation was lifted, after 2004, no clinical infection, incidence of the report.

Just now, the Wuhan Health Commission announced that pneumonia of unknown cause is viral pneumonia, 27 cases have been found so far, of which 7 cases are in serious condition, the remaining cases are stable and controllable, and 2 cases are expected to be discharged in the near future. So far, no obvious human-to-human transmission has been found and no infection among medical staff has been found. At present, the detection of pathogens and the investigation of the causes of infection is under way.

Pneumonia of unknown cause was a concept that appeared in a document of the then Ministry of Health in 2004, after the SARS incident. To screen for possible SARS cases, human cases of avian influenza and other infectious diseases, early warning and appropriate prevention and control measures should be taken, the respiratory disease said, in order to prevent the spread of SARS and possible Human Avian Influenza epidemic, the Ministry of Health has recently formulated the "National Unknown Cause Pneumonia Case Surveillance Implementation Program (trial) . ".

Since the release of the document, pneumonia of unknown cause has been repeatedly detected across the country, but it has not spread widely.

The outbreak in Wuhan was tense because a gene sequencing company had come to Wuhan for preliminary tests that turned out to be highly probable for SARS, according to a person familiar with the matter. But this is not the end result, there are many types of coronavirus, is only a high suspicion. "The National Health Commission has stepped in, and according to the procedure, the virus will be brought back to Beijing, and several tests will be compared to confirm the final result. "

"It is understood that there have been similar highly suspicious but ultimately ruled-out cases in other regions this year. Let's wait and see and there is no need to panic, " said another person familiar with the situation.

This morning, anti-virus concept shares rose, Lu anti-pharmaceutical, Lianhuan pharmaceutical, Rhein biology and Tetraloop biology, four shares rose limit.

Last night, two red-headed documents bearing the seal of the Wuhan Health Commission's Medical Administration went viral on the Internet. Wuhan's south China Seafood Market has been inundated with pneumonia cases of unknown origin, the document said.

An "urgent notice of the Municipal Health and Health Commission on reporting the treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause" requires all units to check patients with pneumonia of unknown cause who have recently visited or worked near the south China Seafood Market, and reported to the Wuhan City Health Commission Medical Administration Office.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Another titled "On doing a good job of unexplained pneumonia emergency notice, " said that some medical institutions in succession appear unexplained pneumonia patients. All medical institutions should strengthen the management of out-patient and emergency care, strictly implement the first-visit responsibility system, find unknown pneumonia patients actively mobilize the strength of local treatment. To be targeted to strengthen the breathing, infection, critical care medicine, such as multidisciplinary professional strength, smooth green channel.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"The hospital did receive these two documents, " the chief doctor of a third-tier Hospital in Wuhan told eight o'clock Jianwen, who was already investigating suspected cases. A doctor in charge of the Wuhan Union Hospital also said that at present it was pneumonia of unknown cause and that the pathogen had not been identified and could not be identified as the SARS virus.

At 8 a.m. on Dec. 31, Jianwen called the Wuhan Center for Disease Control and Prevention and learned that the current progress was still confirming pneumonia, but that SARS had not yet been confirmed. The National Health Commission has sent experts to Wuhan. At present, the related virus typing detection, isolation treatment, public opinion control, terminal disinfection and other work is in progress.

This afternoon, at eight o'clock, a friend of Jianwen arrived at the south China Seafood City and saw that it was still operating normally.

PNEUMONIA OF UNKNOWN CAUSE: The focus of surveillance in the post-SARS era

Pathogen-specific pneumonia is often in the clinical manifestations of a certain regularity, such as pneumococcal pneumonia have fever, cough, small lung auscultation blister sound, chest film showing Patchy Shadow, can be called typical pneumonia.

In contrast, pneumonia, characterized by fever, cough, lung auscultation, and chest x rays, is referred to as Atypical pneumonia, and generally refers to any pneumonia caused by an unknown pathogen, it may be a symptom of pneumonia caused by coronavirus, Mycoplasma PNEUMONIAE, Chlamydophila pneumoniae, or Legionella PNEUMOPHILA, or it may be a general symptom of pneumonia not caused by bacteria.

Atypical pneumonia is not a terrible disease, nor is it a "terminal illness" , just a transitional name until a definitive pathogen has been identified.

Pneumonia of unknown cause is a term put forward by the Ministry of Health in order to better detect and deal with SARS, human avian influenza and other pneumonia with similar and infectious symptoms in time after SARS epidemic. Technically, "unexplained pneumonia" is not a strict medical concept, but as a means of timely detection of suspected cases, early warning and appropriate preventive and control measures.

In particular, pneumonia of unknown cause is defined as a combination of the following four undiagnosed cases of pneumonia:

1. Fever (≥38 °C) ;
2. Imaging features of pneumonia or Acute respiratory distress syndrome;
3. The total white blood cell count in the early stage of the disease is reduced or normal, or the lymphocyte count is reduced;
4. After 3-5 days of Standard Antibiotic Treatment, there was no obvious improvement.

1. Fever (≥38 °C) ;

2. Imaging features of pneumonia or Acute respiratory distress syndrome;

3. The total white blood cell count in the early stage of the disease is reduced or normal, or the lymphocyte count is reduced;

4. After 3-5 days of Standard Antibiotic Treatment, there was no obvious improvement.

SARS and human avian influenza are two types of cases that require priority early warning in cases of unexplained pneumonia. According to the National Implementation Program for the surveillance of cases of pneumonia of unknown cause (pilot) issued by the former Ministry of Health in 2004, cases of pneumonia of unknown cause that meet one of the following conditions can be classified as early warning cases of SARS:

1. Expert Group consultation at prefecture and city level can not exclude cases of pneumonia of unknown cause caused by SARS;
2. Two or more cases of pneumonia of unknown origin with a suspected epidemiological link;
3. Cases of pneumonia of unknown cause in key populations: cases of pneumonia of unknown cause among staff of medical institutions, cases of pneumonia of unknown origin in persons who may have been exposed to the SARS virus or potentially infectious materials (such as those involved in SARS scientific research, testing, reagent and Vaccine Production) , cases of pneumonia of unknown origin in persons exposed to wild animals;
4. UNEXPLAINED PNEUMONIA deaths.

According to the report of Wuhan Health and viral pneumonia, it is more common in winter and spring, and can spread or break out and become epidemic. The main clinical manifestations are fever, aching all over, a small part has difficulty in breathing, and infiltrating shadow in the lungs. Viral pneumonia is associated with virulence, route of infection, and host age and immune status. The viruses causing viral pneumonia are commonly influenza, others are parainfluenza, Cytomegalovirus, adenoviruses, rhinovirus, coronavirus, etc. . Diagnosis depends on etiological tests, including virus isolation, serological tests, and detection of viral antigens and nucleic acids. The disease can be prevented and controlled, to prevent indoor ventilation, to avoid closed, poor ventilation in public places and crowded places, go out can wear a mask. Symptomatic treatment is the main clinical need to rest in bed. If you have any of the above symptoms, especially if you have a persistent fever, see your healthcare provider.
